   - Any trajectory bounds properly throw confidence checks (must remain floating bounds `0` <= `self` <= `1`), along with validating anchor locations exist in graph nodes.
5. **CLI Adjustments (`main.py`)**:
   `GraphValidator(graph).validate()` wraps generation logic naturally, throwing clear list loops of `[ERROR]` and `[WARN]` to mimic deterministic compiler failure output over traditional parsed structures whenever validation detects an issue.

The validation architecture operates entirely independent of the mutation logic of `Pass 1-3`, acting as a purely diagnostic IR assertion block!
